The paper deals with a communication channel affected by bursty interference, which is a topic typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also considers the impact of channel-state information (CSI) on the achievable rates, which is a topic studied in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses mathematical tools such as converse and achievability bounds, which are commonly used in the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories.
